Carbon May Rise as July Utility Profits in Germany Jump, New Energy Says

-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-05-16T13:04:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/carbon-may-rise-as-july-utility-profits-in-germany-jump-new-energy-says.html
European Union carbon permits may
advance this week, as profits made by German power utilities in
July surged to their highest in 18 months, said Bloomberg New
Energy Finance.  December carbon allowances may rise to 17.20 euros ($24.32)
a metric ton from 16.80 euros a ton today on the ICE Futures
Europe exchange in  London , analysts including Konrad Hanschmidt
in London said today in an e-mailed research note.  The profit from producing power in  Germany  in July, known
as a clean-dark spread, climbed 11 percent today to 10.74 euros
a megawatt-hour as of 2:20 p.m. Berlin time, the highest level
since Nov. 13, 2009, according to data from brokers and
exchanges compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Mathew Carr in London at 
 m.carr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  